<subSubSection id="83966541FFC8FFC7FF56B474FE07B481" pageId="7" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CB3336CAFFC8FFC7FF56B474FE07B481" blockId="7.[151,1437,459,918]" pageId="7" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="F9F8EAD8FFC8FFC7FF56B474FE84B43E" bold="true" box="[199,328,783,809]" pageId="7" pageNumber="117">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="0C8C4D49FFC8FFC7FEC9B474FD86B43E" authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1975" box="[344,586,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Caenidae" genus="Brasilocaenis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irmleri">
<emphasis id="F9F8EAD8FFC8FFC7FEC9B474FD86B43E" box="[344,586,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="117">Brasilocaenis irmleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to the group of South American 
<taxonomicName id="0C8C4D49FFC8FFC7FBABB474FB6EB43E" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1853" box="[1082,1186,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Caenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Caeninae">Caeninae</taxonomicName>
with apically pointed forceps. It is easily distinguished from all 
<taxonomicName id="0C8C4D49FFC8FFC7FDF7B448FC9BB45A" box="[614,855,819,845]" pageId="7" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="F9F8EAD8FFC8FFC7FDF7B448FCCCB45A" box="[614,768,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="117">Brasilocaenis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the very long styliger plate with posterior margin rounded and forceps enlarged near base and narrow toward the apex, and fused to lateral margins of styliger plate (adapted from 
<bibRefCitation id="AF1D4B3BFFC8FFC7FEADB400FE73B481" author="Puthz, V." box="[316,447,891,918]" pageId="7" pageNumber="117" pagination="411 - 415" refId="ref8627" refString="Puthz, V. (1975) Eine neue Caenidengattung aus dem Amazonasgebiet (Insecta: Ephemeroptera: Caenidae). Amazoniana, 5, 411 - 415." type="journal article" year="1975">Puthz 1975</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
